entries.arrived_at_loc: Hold at your current location. Transmission will begin shortly. Stay near the satellite or we will lose all the data.
entries.attack_notify: pcontrast1 Tactical Computer:pcontrast3 <Warning! Incoming enemy fighters.>
entries.attack_stopped: pcontrast1 Tactical Computer:pcontrast3 <Enemy fighter wing has been eliminated.>
entries.first_attack: pcontrast1 Tactical Computer:pcontrast3 <Warning! Enemy fighters moving into engage.>
entries.found_loc: You should have the satellite location in your nav computer. Proceed to that location immediately for data transmission.
entries.outofrange: Tranmission Progress:<Signal lost. Satellite out of range. Return to reestablish tranmission.>
entries.outofrange_failed: We lost the signal! Pilot you have some explaining to do with your superior as to why you left the area and cost us important information.
entries.quest_defendpoint_d: Once you have arrived at the location, wait for the transmission to begin. You might attract unwanted attention from those who don't want us to get that information, but you will need to remain in the area to make sure that you send a complete transmission.
entries.quest_location_d: The satellite that command wants you to use is located in the Yavin system.
entries.quest_reachpoint_d: Travel to the Nav waypoint given, which will lead you to the Imperial communication satellite.
entries.split_quest_alert: We have the information from the spy's ship. While you are in the sector we need you to pick up some documents on Dr. Shinss' project to compare against his statement. Location of the delivery vessel has been uploaded to your nav computer.
entries.title: Yavin System: Transmit the Data To Headquarters
entries.title_d: Inquisition command wants that data immediately, but there aren't any vessels available to pick it up. You will have to risk transmitting the logs via a satellite. Travel to an Imperial satellite and transmit the data to command.
entries.trans_update: Transmission Progress:<%DI percent of transmission sent.>
entries.transmission_received: Transmission Progress:<Transmission completed. Please stand by.>
entries.transmission_start: Transmission Progress:<Transmission started. Remain in the area to avoid irrepairable data lose.>
